column5: The neighbors stopped by for breakfast this morning this morning and brought the younguns with them
Geez!   What a nice surprise.   Thanksgiving and Christmas dinners delivered fresh to your doorstep.
Yeah, doesn't get much better than that Bruce LOL
My in-laws stop by unexpectedly sometimes too....
My in-laws stop by unexpectedly sometimes too....    Thats cool Lew. Im thinking thats a second hatch .
Tell them to come back Oct 12---they are invited for dinner!!
Dit they gobble up the bugs in your lawn Lew?
Very nice. Always amazes me how the chicks survive predation. The adults can fly and roost in trees. But the young?
You're very lucky to have neighbors like that ! They look a bit disappointed . You killed their breakfast
Great! All I see is buzzards, I think they come to check up on me! Is he done yet? LOL

The young are very strong fliers, no problem at all getting into trees to roost. They make it look easier than the adults do, after all they are only a fraction of the weight of the adults....any 20lb+ bird has to work to get airborne!
Ya but I mean when they are real young
Yeah, pretty vulnerable for the first couple weeks while stuck on the ground. Survival rates go way up once they start flying. I heard some can fly by 10 days.
